                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d415">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 659.119/439c</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-27T21:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 27, 1918, 9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>459. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 942. We are in receipt of a letter from the British Embassy stating that the
                    British Government would not agree to any deduction <pb facs="0502" n="1336"
                        xml:id="pg_1336"/> below 200,000 tons in the amount of tonnage to be placed
                    at the disposal of the Allies under the terms of the proposed agreement with
                    Denmark and that the British Government would not make any concession on account
                    of the 40,000 tons of Danish ships sunk by German submarines while in Allied
                    service. Repeat to Copenhagen.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
